======================================================================
PART 4: POINCARE POLYNOMIAL P(T,t) = sum Omega_k * t^k
  Duality: P(T,t) = t^{n-1} * P(T, 1/t)?
  Equivalently: Omega_k = Omega_{n-1-k}
======================================================================

  Transitive:
    n=7, H=1
    Omega = [7, 21, 35, 35, 21, 7, 1]
    Betti = [1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
    Chi = 1
    sum(Omega) = 127
    Alt sum((-1)^k * Omega_k) = 1
    P(1) = 127 (total dim of path space)
    Omega is 'almost palindromic' (Omega[0:-1] reversed = Omega[-2::-1])

  Paley T_7:
    n=7, H=189
    Omega = [7, 21, 42, 63, 63, 42, 21]
    Betti = [1, 0, 0, 0, 6, 0, 0]
    Chi = 7
    sum(Omega) = 259
    Alt sum((-1)^k * Omega_k) = 7
    P(1) = 259 (total dim of path space)

  Cyclic interval n=5:
    n=5, H=15
    Omega = [5, 10, 10, 10, 5]
    Betti = [1, 1, 0, 0, 0]
    Chi = 0
    sum(Omega) = 40
    Alt sum((-1)^k * Omega_k) = 0
    P(1) = 40 (total dim of path space)
    *** Omega is PALINDROMIC (Poincare duality) ***

